1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with association policies for STAs in a WLAN, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also be relevant to the security of WLANs, as the association policy may affect the security of the network. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve information theory concepts such as throughput and delay, which are relevant to the design of communication systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions web browsing, which involves multimedia content such as images and videos. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a policy for optimizing the performance of a system (WLAN), which may be relevant to the systems and control subcategory.
